                                    Ward D Councilperson Jake Ephros

                                    Term of Office:
                                    First Elected To Council: Dec. 2, 2025 
                                    Current Term Expires: January 14, 2030

                                    201) 547-5485
                                    JEphros@jcnj.org

                                    Council Aide: Bingjiefu He
                                    (201) 547-6817

                                    Biography

                                    Jake Ephros is a proud teacher at Saint Peter's University, a former union organizer, and a democratic socialist in Jersey City Heights. A longtime activist, Jake led Jersey Citys Right To Counsel campaign, which won guaranteed legal representation for tenants in housing court. He fought alongside union nurses and nursing home workers with 1199SEIU to win better contracts and has been active in immigration justice work in Hudson County. Jake is proud to have earned the trust and support of thousands of Ward D residents and is thrilled to begin representing our community on City Council.
